9 the possession of a lessee, and the lessor provides a peace officer with the motor
10 vehicle's registration number and the name, address, and operator's license number of
11 the individual renting or leasing the motor vehicle.
12 5. An individual may not be charged both with violating this section and section 39 - 10 - 71
13 for acts arising out of the same incident or occurrence.
14 6. This section does not apply to a motor vehicle rental company renting motor vehicles
15 to customers for a period of ninety days or less.
